properties.name: Anaheim Hills Home
properties.description: Posted by Adam90014 6432 East Lookout Lane, Anaheim, CA 92807I lived here from about the age of 2-18. I also lived in Huntington Beach at the same time, across the county. Anaheim Hills is an interesting place. I could never people I lived there without people rolling their eyes are making some sort of comment like "oh wow, you must be rich". Yes, it was a very nice area. But we also didn\'t have a grand estate.

properties.name: Downtown Santa Barbara Home
properties.description: Posted by Adam90014 1501 Santa Barbara Street, Santa Barbara, CA I moved here to get away from Isla Vista. It was a fantastic move. The apartment was immense and had the best view you could ask for. Notable memories: pissing off the lesbians downstairs about every five minutes.

properties.name: Echo Park Recreation Center and Tennis Courts
properties.description: Posted by Adam90014 1632 Bellevue Ave, Los Angeles, CAInteresting courts on the other side of the freeway. Quite an audience of high school dropouts, the homeless and crazy people. Nice.

properties.name: Huntington Beach Home
properties.description: Posted by Adam90014   1516 Pacific Coast Highway, Huntington Beach, CA 92648One day my parents came home and they told us they bought a second home at the beach at an auction. It was random. Huntington Beach is/was a great place. Perfectly small town, but also has a lot of interesting people/sites. My parents didn\'t want us to have our teen years there, though, due to the excessive bar/club scene down there.

properties.name: Isla Vista Apartment
properties.description: Posted by Adam90014 This place blew. The apartment was shit and it wasn\'t the best year. I couldn\'t wait to get out of IV and move on to Santa Barbara.

properties.name: Los Angeles Home
properties.description: Posted by Adam90014 610 South Main Street, Los Angeles, CA 90014Pacific Electric Lofts. Best place I\'ve llived so far. Good people, great loft, fun area, no complaints.

properties.name: Mater Dei High School
properties.description: Posted by Adam90014 1202 West Edinger, Santa Ana, CAOh high school. Good school academically, athletically, artistically, but man oh man, you couldn\'t pay me enough to go back to high school.

properties.name: PCC Tennis Courts
properties.description: Posted by Adam90014 1570 E. Colorado Blvd. Pasadena, CAA much better place to play tennis than Echo Park. Not as many "cultural elements" though.
